Subject: Re: [T2] Brake booster shot?

On Mon, 10 Sep 2007, Jason Meyer wrote:
> After I started my van, I started pumping the brake and noticed that when I
> pumped the brake, the engine struggled. However, when I took my foot off the
> brake, it idled fine.

This might be normal.  The booster works by allowing the engine to pull
air from its chamber and pumping the brake allows the engine to do this
over and over, leaning out the mixture.
